# ============================================================================
# Notes:
# ============================================================================
# 1. All sensitive keys (DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, API keys) are kept secret
#    and only accessible on the backend (Vercel serverless functions).
#
# 2. Public configuration (TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY, ENABLE_PREMIUM, etc.) is
#    served to the frontend via the /api/config endpoint.
#
# 3. No VITE_ prefix needed! The useConfig() hook fetches public config
#    from the API, keeping secrets secure.
#
# 4. For production deployment on Vercel:
#    - Add all these variables to Vercel Environment Variables
#    - Update APP_DOMAIN to your production domain
#    - Generate a new JWT_SECRET for production
#    - Never expose API keys in frontend code
# ============================================================================

